name: Salesforce Sales Cloud
description: Add a Salesforce Instance to connect your existing Salesforce account to the CRM Hub, allowing you to manage contacts, leads, accounts, opportunities etc. across multiple CRM Elements or your other Salesforce services. You will need your Salesforce account information to add an instance.
configDescription: If you do not have a Salesforce.com account, you can create one at Salesforce.com Signup

parameters.description: The ID of the object

parameters.name: objectName
parameters.description: The object name of the object to be retrieved. Supported attachment objects are Account, Asset, Campaign, Case, Contact, Contract, Custom objects, EmailMessage, EmailTemplate, Event, Lead, Opportunity, Product2, Solution and Task.

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The start page for pagination, which defaults to 1 if not supplied

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size for pagination, which defaults to 200 if not supplied

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. For example, to search for accounts last modified on or after 'Jan 15, 2014', the search expression will be where=lastModifiedDate>='2014-01-15T00:00:00.000Z'. When this parameter is omitted, all accounts are returned in a paginated fashion.

objects.name: accounts
objects.description: Represents an individual account, which is an organization or person involved with your business (such as customers, competitors, and partners)

objects.name: accountsActivities
objects.description: Represents an event in the calendar for an account. In the user interface, event and task records are collectively referred to as activities

objects.name: accountsNotes
objects.description: Represents a note, which is text associated with an account object

objects.name: accountsTasks
objects.description: Represents a business activity such as making a phone call or other to-do items. In the user interface, Task and Event records are collectively referred to as activities.

objects.name: attachments
objects.description: Represents a file that a User has uploaded and attached to a parent object.

objects.name: attachmentsData
objects.description: The binary data of an attachment

objects.name: campaigns
objects.description: Represents and tracks a marketing campaign, such as a direct mail promotion, webinar, or trade show.

objects.name: contacts
objects.description: Represents a contact, which is a person associated with an account.

objects.name: contactsActivities
objects.description: Represents an event in the calendar for a contact. In the user interface, event and task records are collectively referred to as activities.

objects.name: contactsNotes
objects.description: Represents a note, which is text associated with a contact

objects.name: contactsTasks
objects.description: Represents a business activity such as making a phone call or other to-do items. In the user interface, Task and Event records are collectively referred to as activities.

objects.name: data
objects.description: The binary data of an object such as a document or attachment

objects.name: fields
objects.description: The fields for a given object

objects.name: filesDetails
objects.description: The metadata about a specific ContentVersion

objects.name: filesVersions
objects.description: The available versions for a specified contentVersion

objects.name: filesVersionsLatestVersion
objects.description: The binary data of the latest version of the Document or Attachment

objects.name: filesVersionsLatestVersionMetadata
objects.description: The metadata about the latest version of a Document

objects.name: filesVersionsMetadata
objects.description: Represents a specific version of a document in Salesforce CRM Content or Salesforce Files. This object is available in versions 17.0 and later for Salesforce CRM Content documents. This object is available in versions 20.0 and later for Salesforce Files.

objects.name: leads
objects.description: Represents a prospect or lead

objects.name: leadsActivities
objects.description: Represents an event in the calendar for a lead. In the user interface, event and task records are collectively referred to as activities.

objects.name: leadsNotes
objects.description: Represents a note, which is text associated with a lead

objects.name: leadsTasks
objects.description: Represents a business activity such as making a phone call or other to-do items. In the user interface, Task and Event records are collectively referred to as activities.

objects.name: notes
objects.description: Represents a note, which is text associated with a custom object or a standard object

objects.name: opportunities
objects.description: Represents an opportunity, which is a sale or pending deal

objects.name: opportunitiesActivities
objects.description: Represents an event in the calendar for an opportunity. In the user interface, event and task records are collectively referred to as activities.

objects.name: opportunitiesNotes
objects.description: Represents a note, which is text associated with an opportunity

objects.name: reportTypes
objects.description: The available types of reports as configured in the CRM system

objects.name: reports
objects.description: In its simplest form, a report is a list of records (like opportunities or accounts) that meet the criteria you define

objects.name: reportsMetadata
objects.description: View available reports in the CRM system

objects.name: users
objects.description: Represents a user in your organization

objects.name: usersMe
objects.description: Details about the authenticated user

objects.name: filesMetadata
objects.description: Detailed metadata about a specific ContentVersion

objects.name: files
objects.description: Represents a document that has been uploaded to a library in Salesforce CRM Content or Salesforce Files. This object is available in versions 17.0 and later for Salesforce CRM Content. This object is available in API version 21.0 and later for Salesforce Files
